<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13070924/rail-holidays-in-italy.jpg" alt="Rail Holidays in Italy" data-udi="umb://media/13070924/rail-holidays-in-italy.jpg" /></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title"><span>Travelling to and around Italy by rail is easy, cost-effective and can be a great way to see the country. High-speed rail lines between major cities means you can be sipping a coffee in St. Mark’s Square in the morning and touring the Ufizzi Gallery by the afternoon. We can arrange all elements of your itinerary, book train tickets and give advice on the spectacular journey’s you wouldn’t want to miss out on.</span></span></p>
<div class="data-grid" style="float: center;">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="tablet-button" style="height: 50px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td height="20" align="center" valign="middle" style="background-color: #89aa4d; border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; background-clip: padding-box; font-size: 18px; font-family: arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; color: #ffffff; font-weight: bold; padding-left: 18px; padding-right: 18px;">For more information or to book a <a data-udi="umb://document/75608f96f365422d89a1d50cd6c3339e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/75608f96f365422d89a1d50cd6c3339e}" title="Multi-Centre Holidays">multi-centre holidays</a> &amp; <a data-udi="umb://document/731184fa7b9742f0a969771e90773289" href="/{localLink:umb://document/731184fa7b9742f0a969771e90773289}" title="Tours and Multi-Centre Holidays">tours</a> please call 01483 79 11 11</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>
</div>
</div>
<p align="center"><span class="page-title"><a name="backtotop"></a>Trains from the UK to Italy</span></p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13071028/cinque_terre_italy.jpg" alt="Cinque Terre in Italy" data-udi="umb://media/cb110f6e066f4c5ab0c4a15cfc5d5fa2" /></p>
<p><span>Travelling from London to Italy by train is easy thanks to services from Eurostar to Paris and from Voyages SNCF onwards to Italy. From Paris, daytime services include a journey to <a data-udi="umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd}" title="Milan">Milan</a> or a high-speed train that travels through the Swiss Alps to <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48" href="/{localLink:umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48}" title="Lake Maggiore">Lake Maggiore</a>. Overnight services depart from Paris in the early evening and arrive into Italy by morning. Cabins are available with two or three berths and they come equipped with a wash basin.</span></p>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p align="center"><span class="page-title">high speed trains</span></p>
<p><img src="/media/13070922/rail-holidays-in-italy-2.jpg" alt="Rail Holidays in Italy" data-udi="umb://media/302e5c6c42304e45b91a80306d43eb2c" /></p>
<p>Trenitalia’s great network of high-speed rail routes makes touring Italy a breeze. Major cities are all connected, from <a data-udi="umb://document/65aa4a2626424153a1c1c3685d2607aa" href="/{localLink:umb://document/65aa4a2626424153a1c1c3685d2607aa}" title="Turin">Turin</a> all the way down to Salerno, and this is the best and most comfortable way to get between them. Services are frequent and carriages well equipped. You’ll be assigned a seat and have plenty of leg room to sit back and relax on your journey. If you book first class you’ll even be treated to a glass of prosecco as you embark.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p align="center"><span class="page-title">Regional Trains</span></p>
<p><img src="/media/13070923/rail-holidays-in-italy-3.jpg" alt="Regional Rail Holidays in Italy" data-udi="umb://media/1d95776134e944e0b98db173adf0e733" /></p>
<p><span>These trains are perfect for onward travel to smaller towns like <a data-udi="umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec}" title="Siena &amp; Chianti">Siena</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/56a6c9526dcb4eada10b90c88147868c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/56a6c9526dcb4eada10b90c88147868c}" title="Tuscany Coast">Viareggio</a>. They have a slower pace so you’ll get to enjoy a bit of scenery before arriving at your destination. It’s also a great way to explore more of Italy on your holiday with day trips by train. From <a data-udi="umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7}" title="Venice">Venice,</a> take the train to Vicenza, head to Lucca from Florence or jump on at <a data-udi="umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8}" title="Sorrento">Sorrento</a> for a quick ride to Pompeii or <a data-udi="umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9}" title="Naples">Naples</a>. </span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow" style="text-align: center;"><span class="geolocation-title">Create your own rail holiday with the help of our expert team. Call 01483 79 11 11</span></div>
</div>
